Both deliverables are written and the transcript validates against the schema (25 iterations, 35 hypotheses, 34 analyses).

**Key finding:** `feature_027` is a beneficial treatment whose efficacy is concentrated in a four-predicate biomarker-favorable subgroup:

> `feature_006=0 AND feature_023=0 AND feature_022=0 AND feature_005 ≤ 5`

- Within favorable subgroup (n=9,338, ~19% of cohort): **+5.01 months PFS**, p < 1e-300
- Outside (n=40,662): +0.02 months, p=0.36 (null)
- Adding the (tx × favorable) interaction lifts model R² from 0.86 → 0.99
- All four predicates are jointly necessary (sensitivity-tested by dropping each)
- Treatment allocation is balanced across subgroups (20.4% vs 20.0%), so the heterogeneity is genuine biomarker-conditional efficacy, not selection
- An apparent `feature_011` modifier (p=1e-11 marginally) was diagnosed as confounded — within the favorable subgroup it disappears (p=0.31)
- A greedy variance-maximizing tree search independently recovered the same four-predicate subgroup

Major prognostic factors (`feature_015`, `feature_001`, `feature_014`, `feature_019`, `feature_025`) are strong but treatment-independent — they form a stable prognostic backbone.
